quran[3]{c,v,t,f}:
  2,246,"Have you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>not seen the chiefs of the Children of Israel after Moses, when they said to a prophet of theirs, “Appoint a king for us, and we will combat in the way of Allah.”? He said, “Would you perhaps, in case combat is prescribed upon you, not combat?” They said, “Why would we not combat in the way of Allah when we were evicted from our homes along with our children?” But when combat was prescribed upon them, they turned away, except for a few of them. For Allah is All-Knowing of the unjust<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>."
  2,247,"Thus their prophet said to them, “Indeed, Allah has sent you Talut{1}as a king.” They said, “How can he have authority over us when we are more worthy of authority than he, for he was not brought abundance of wealth?” He said, “Allah has chosen him over you and has increased him in knowledge and build.” Thus Allah brings His authority to whomever He wills, for Allah is All-Embracing, All-Knowing.",footnotes:1:Saul.
  2,248,"And their prophet said to them, “Indeed, the sign of his authority is that the ark{1}shall come to you with tranquility from your Lord, and relics left by Moses’s folk and Aaron’s folk.<i class=""s"">(It shall be) </i>carried by the angels. In that is a sign for you, if you have been believers.”",footnotes:1:Of the covenant.
